If master/msgidsuffix isn't in the configuration file, it defaults to
"@hostname".
Bumped version number to 1.06, updated NEWS and manual pages.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r251 | fabrice.colin@gmail.com | 2011-11-29 14:48:11 +0100 (Tue, 29 Nov 2011) | 5 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/src/DBStatusUpdater.cc
   M /trunk/src/DBStatusUpdater.h
   M /trunk/src/LibESMTPProvider.cc
   M /trunk/src/LibETPANProvider.cc
   M /trunk/src/SMTPOptions.cc
   M /trunk/src/SMTPOptions.h
   M /trunk/src/SMTPProvider.cc
   M /trunk/src/SMTPProvider.h
   M /trunk/src/SMTPSession.cc
   M /trunk/src/StatusUpdater.cc
   M /trunk/src/StatusUpdater.h
   M /trunk/src/givemail.cc

Option -d/--dump-file instructs givemail to write to disk the plain text and
HTML parts of messages loaded with -x/--xml-file, as sent to recipients. Files
are keyed by message ID, with extension txt or html.
Message IDs are saved to the status file.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r250 | fabrice.colin@gmail.com | 2011-11-23 05:00:12 +0100 (Wed, 23 Nov 2011) | 2 lines
