------------------------------------------------------------------------
r159 | fabrice.colin | 2009-10-13 14:44:08 +0200 (Tue, 13 Oct 2009) | 5 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/src/LibESMTPProvider.cc
   M /trunk/src/LibETPANProvider.cc
   M /trunk/src/MessageDetails.cc
   M /trunk/src/MessageDetails.h
   M /trunk/src/csv2givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.cc
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.1
   M /trunk/src/webapi-key-manager.1

When driven by a file passed with -x/--xml-file, one can set the prefix of
(Resent-)Message-Id with -m/--message-id-prefix, or that of References and
In-Reply-To if -e/--reply is set, instead of getting a random value.
The suffix is provided by the configuration file, under "master/msgidsuffix".

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r158 | fabrice.colin | 2009-09-19 06:06:04 +0200 (Sat, 19 Sep 2009) | 7 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/conf/givemail.conf
   M /trunk/configure.in
   M /trunk/givemail.spec.in
   M /trunk/src/ConfigurationFile.cc
   M /trunk/src/ConfigurationFile.h
   M /trunk/src/DomainAuth.h
   M /trunk/src/DomainKeys.cc
   M /trunk/src/DomainKeys.h
   A /trunk/src/LibESMTPProvider.cc
   A /trunk/src/LibESMTPProvider.h
   A /trunk/src/LibETPANProvider.cc
   A /trunk/src/LibETPANProvider.h
   M /trunk/src/Makefile.am
   M /trunk/src/MessageDetails.cc
   M /trunk/src/MessageDetails.h
   A /trunk/src/SMTPProvider.cc
   A /trunk/src/SMTPProvider.h
   M /trunk/src/SMTPSession.cc
   M /trunk/src/SMTPSession.h
   M /trunk/src/Substitute.cc
   M /trunk/src/Substitute.h
   M /trunk/src/TestFile.cc
   M /trunk/src/csv2givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.cc
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.1
   M /trunk/src/webapi-key-manager.1
   M /trunk/src/webapi-key-manager.cc

Refactored and separated libestmp dependent code from the rest. SMTPProvider is
the interface that builds and sends messages, and is implemented by both
LibESMTPProvider and LibETPANProvider.
Which SMTP provider is used at runtime depends on the configuration item
"slave/smtpprovider" as well as the configure options "--enable-libesmtp" and
"--enable-libetpan".

