------------------------------------------------------------------------
r144 | fabrice.colin | 2009-08-10 06:15:12 +0200 (Mon, 10 Aug 2009) | 2 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/sample-emails/test.xml

Illustrate customfield usage.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r143 | fabrice.colin | 2009-08-10 06:14:21 +0200 (Mon, 10 Aug 2009) | 8 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/src/TestFile.cc
   M /trunk/src/TestFile.h
   M /trunk/src/csv2givemail.cc
   M /trunk/src/givemail.cc

TestFile can parse a memory buffer too, looks for customfield elements.
This allows givemail (not in slave mode) to look for substitution fields in
the XML file passed with -x, or passed with the new -f parameter. When set
to "stdin", the XML is read from standard input.
One could use "-x some_file_on_disk" and "-f stdin" to feed fields generated
dynamically by an application.
Synced csv2givemail with TestFile.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r142 | fabrice.colin | 2009-08-09 17:00:07 +0200 (Sun, 09 Aug 2009) | 2 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/givemail.spec.in

SELinux support.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r141 | fabrice.colin | 2009-08-09 16:58:15 +0200 (Sun, 09 Aug 2009) | 2 lines
