------------------------------------------------------------------------
r19 | fabrice.colin | 2009-04-01 15:30:02 +0200 (Wed, 01 Apr 2009) | 2 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.cc

This should have been in the previous commit.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r18 | fabrice.colin | 2009-04-01 15:27:39 +0200 (Wed, 01 Apr 2009) | 17 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/README
   M /trunk/src/CampaignSQL.cc
   M /trunk/src/CampaignSQL.h
   M /trunk/src/SMTPSession.cc
   M /trunk/src/SMTPSession.h
   M /trunk/src/WebAPI.cc
   M /trunk/src/csv2givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.cc
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.1

Modified CampaignSQL::listDomains() to either skip Sent domains, or all but
Waiting. The latter mode is enabled by passing "-w/--waiting-only" to givemail.
This is used by the daemon when restarting slaves.

Overloaded CampaignSQL::getRecipients() to not retrieve the total count of
matching recipients. This overload doesn't support offsets and is called by
givemail, while a tweaked version of the original is called by the Web API.

In SMTPSession, smtp_start_session() is mutex'ed if the environment variable
GIVEMAIL_MUTEX_SESSIONS is set to "Y". GNUnet source indicates that it's not
thread-safe, but in practice it seems okay.

SMTPSession records libesmtp errors on smtp_start_session(). It's saved to
each failed recipient's staus by givemail.

Updated manual pages and README.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r17 | fabrice.colin | 2009-03-29 15:35:47 +0200 (Sun, 29 Mar 2009) | 2 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.cc

Fix for previous check-in.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r16 | fabrice.colin | 2009-03-29 15:21:15 +0200 (Sun, 29 Mar 2009) | 3 lines
Changed paths:
   M /trunk/scripts/givemaild
   M /trunk/src/csv2givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemail.1
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.1
   M /trunk/src/givemaild.cc

If the option --restart-slaves is passed, slaves killed by SIGSEGV are restarted
by the daemon. The service script enables this.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
